CardNames.1:
Feudal Courts

Q: Where does the Court token go when I secure a card with it?
A: If you're a Lord, return it to the general supply. If you're a Vassal, keep it on the refilled card.
CardNames.4:
Skirmishers

Q: Can I reroll this multiple times?
A: No, only once.
CardNames.7:
Warden's Levy

Q: Which hits to the ships on the card take?
A: The ships are on the card take hits for self-hit damage (flame icons and intercept)
CardNames.11:
Lord of the 6th Cluster

Q: In a Closed Economy, can a Regent Lord tax a Vassal City under Imperial control?
A: No. A Regent Lord is bound by the Truce law when taxing a Regent Vassal city under Imperial control, and bound by Closed Economy when taxing an Outlaw Vassal city under Imperial control. An Outlaw Lord can always tax Vassal cities regardless of Empire control.
